# Models Layer Rules

## Role
Models represent data entities, define relationships, and serve as pure data containers. All business logic has been moved to dedicated services for clean separation of concerns.

## Should Do
- **Data structure**: Define table structure with proper column types and constraints
- **Relationships**: Define entity relationships and foreign keys using SQLAlchemy relationships
- **Database constraints**: Use unique constraints, indexes, and foreign key constraints
- **Data representation**: Provide `__repr__` methods for debugging and logging
- **Column documentation**: Document field purposes with comments (SYSTEM, MANUAL, CALCULATED)

## Shouldn't Do
- **Business logic**: Delegate all business logic to services
- **Validation methods**: Delegate validation to validation services
- **Calculations**: Delegate calculations to calculator classes
- **External service calls**: Keep models focused on data only
- **HTTP concerns**: Handle request/response formatting (controllers)
- **Database operations**: Delegate all database operations to repositories

## Examples

```python
# ✅ Good: Pure data container with proper structure
class Bank(Base):
    """Model representing a banking institution."""
    
    __tablename__ = "banks"
    
    # Primary key and basic fields
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)  # (SYSTEM) auto-generated primary key
    name = Column(String(255), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) bank name
    country = Column(Enum(Country), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
    bank_type = Column(Enum(BankType), nullable=True)  # (MANUAL) bank type
    swift_bic = Column(String(11), nullable=True)  # (MANUAL) optional SWIFT/BIC identifier
    
    # System timestamps
    created_at = Column(DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow)  # (SYSTEM) creation timestamp
    updated_at = Column(DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow, onupdate=datetime.utcnow)  # (SYSTEM) last update timestamp
    
    # Calculated fields (updated by services)
    status = Column(Enum(BankStatus), nullable=True)  # (CALCULATED) bank status
    current_number_of_bank_accounts = Column(Integer, default=0)  # (CALCULATED) total number of bank accounts
    current_balance_in_bank_accounts = Column(Float, default=0.0)  # (CALCULATED) total balance of all bank accounts
    
    # Relationships
    accounts = relationship("BankAccount", back_populates="bank", cascade="all, delete-orphan")
    
    def __repr__(self) -> str:
        return f"<Bank(id={self.id}, name='{self.name}', country='{self.country}', bank_type='{self.bank_type}')>"

# ✅ Good: Model with constraints and indexes
class BankAccount(Base):
    """Model representing an investor-owned bank account."""
    
    __tablename__ = "bank_accounts"
    
    # Primary key and foreign keys
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)  # (SYSTEM) auto-generated primary key
    entity_id = Column(Integer, ForeignKey("entities.id"), nullable=False, index=True)  # (MANUAL) owner entity
    bank_id = Column(Integer, ForeignKey("banks.id"), nullable=False, index=True)  # (MANUAL) linked bank
    
    # Account details
    account_name = Column(String(255), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) human-readable account name/label
    account_number = Column(String(64), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) account number stored as provided
    currency = Column(Enum(Currency), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) ISO-4217 currency code
    account_type = Column(Enum(BankAccountType), nullable=False)  # (MANUAL) account type
    
    # System timestamps
    created_at = Column(DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow)  # (SYSTEM) creation timestamp
    updated_at = Column(DateTime, default=datetime.utcnow, onupdate=datetime.utcnow)  # (SYSTEM) last update timestamp
    
    # Calculated fields
    status = Column(Enum(BankAccountStatus), nullable=True)  # (CALCULATED) account status
    current_balance = Column(Float, default=0.0)  # (CALCULATED) current balance of the account
    
    # Database constraints
    __table_args__ = (
        UniqueConstraint("entity_id", "bank_id", "account_number", name="uq_bank_account_unique"),
        UniqueConstraint("bank_id", "account_number", name="uq_bank_account_number_unique"),
    )
    
    # Relationships
    bank = relationship("Bank", back_populates="accounts")
    entity = relationship("Entity", back_populates="bank_accounts")
    
    def __repr__(self) -> str:
        return (
            f"<BankAccount(id={self.id}, entity_id={self.entity_id}, bank_id={self.bank_id}, "
            f"name='{self.account_name}', number='{self.account_number}', currency='{self.currency}')>"
        )

# ❌ Bad: Business logic in model
class Bank(Base):
    def validate_bank_data(self) -> bool:
        if not self.name:
            raise ValueError("Bank name is required")  # Business logic - should be in validation service
        return True
    
    def calculate_total_balance(self, session: Session) -> float:
        # Complex calculation - should be in calculator class
        return sum(account.balance for account in self.accounts)

# ❌ Bad: External service calls in model
class Bank(Base):
    def send_notification(self):
        # External service call - should be in service layer
        notification_service.send_bank_created_notification(self)
